51:50.158 --> 51:52.907
"You, young American,
do not know them..."

51:52.908 --> 51:54.425
Waiting...

51:56.341 --> 51:58.666
What if you read with the other voice?

52:00.058 --> 52:03.058
- What voice?
- A poet, Pablo.

52:06.225 --> 52:09.808
"You, young American,
do not know them."

52:10.575 --> 52:14.791
They are the dark
vampires of our skies.

52:15.450 --> 52:18.782
Bitter the shadows of their wings.

52:18.783 --> 52:22.925
"Pris es, martyr,
death, gave..."

52:26.850 --> 52:28.491
- Finished?
- Yes Yes.

52:31.225 --> 52:33.525
- Where are we going?
- Valparaíso.

52:33.526 --> 52:34.974
Thank you.

52:34.975 --> 52:40.210
The senator needs to wait for
a Chinese merchant ship.

52:40.211 --> 52:41.311
AND...

52:42.058 --> 52:44.700
Delia, they do not
allow women on board.

52:51.241 --> 52:52.541
My love...

52:54.641 --> 52:56.041
All right, dear.

52:59.183 --> 53:00.383
Excuse.

53:06.666 --> 53:09.466
Good... we'll talk.

53:12.158 --> 53:14.566
- Good trip.
- Thank you, Victor.

53:17.083 --> 53:18.483
My love...

53:21.516 --> 53:22.916
I will not cry.

53:43.683 --> 53:47.158
A good cop would follow him
to the fugitive's house.

53:48.225 --> 53:50.050
But I'm a bad cop.

53:50.433 --> 53:54.216
I like it when the suspects
confess with whispers or shouts.

53:58.350 --> 54:00.366
"Come and be with me, brother."

54:01.158 --> 54:05.033
Give me your hand, from the
depths of your disseminated pain.

54:05.725 --> 54:08.482
You will not come back from
the bottom of the rocks.

54:08.483 --> 54:11.399
You will not return
from underground time.

54:11.400 --> 54:14.324
Your angry voice will not return.

54:14.325 --> 54:16.825
"They shall not return
thine eyes pierced..."

54:21.616 --> 54:23.616
"Here I was punished."

54:29.866 --> 54:31.657
Because the jewelry did not shine.

54:31.658 --> 54:34.991
"And the earth did not deliver the
stone and the grain in due time."

54:36.033 --> 54:39.658
"I come to speak through
your dead mouth."

54:40.325 --> 54:42.857
Like a river of buried tigers.

54:42.858 --> 54:48.758
And let me cry for
hours, days, years.

54:49.450 --> 54:52.899
"Blind ages, stellar centuries."

54:52.900 --> 54:56.992
Strangely...
I believe in you.

54:56.993 --> 54:58.293
I believe.

54:58.732 --> 55:01.290
I am glad.
I was the first to say:

55:01.291 --> 55:04.540
"Pablo, if you go to
trial, you will win."

55:04.541 --> 55:06.307
So let's go get him together.

55:06.308 --> 55:08.990
But I do not know where, they
do not tell me anything.

55:08.991 --> 55:10.324
Because?

55:10.325 --> 55:12.607
They distrust me because
I'm not Chilean.

55:12.608 --> 55:13.974
I understand.

55:13.975 --> 55:16.575
Let's stay in touch, maybe
I'll find out something.

55:16.576 --> 55:18.102
Yes wait.

55:18.866 --> 55:21.449
We just learned that
Neruda left Chile.

55:22.158 --> 55:24.575
- Really?
- Yeah, he left.

55:26.266 --> 55:27.566
How incredible.

55:29.491 --> 55:30.791
Because?

55:31.450 --> 55:33.908
Because you're watching
over the borders.

55:36.850 --> 55:38.991
Do you think he's still in Chile?

55:40.158 --> 55:42.658
No, he must be outside.

55:52.958 --> 55:54.699
I'm going to Valparaíso.

55:54.700 --> 55:56.516
Do not. Because?

55:57.058 --> 55:58.783
To see if anyone saw him leave.

56:00.408 --> 56:02.640
I think he's still in Chile.

56:02.641 --> 56:05.116
But he just said he was abroad.

56:06.325 --> 56:09.958
Do not. You said that
he had escaped by ship.

56:10.891 --> 56:14.391
This is a good example of
a whispered confession.

56:18.475 --> 56:22.408
The lucidity of the policeman overcomes
the stupidity of the Spaniard.

56:34.758 --> 56:36.933
What looks so much out the window?

56:37.758 --> 56:39.058
People.

56:43.383 --> 56:45.825
"Is this silk?"
- No.

56:46.457 --> 56:47.657
So what is it?

56:47.658 --> 56:50.541
A sailor traded the cloth
for 12 bottles of wine.

56:52.124 --> 56:53.424
Good business.

56:53.425 --> 56:56.857
The poet will always applaud
an unfair exchange.

56:56.858 --> 56:59.157
Do I have to pretend
I'm a sailor?

56:59.158 --> 57:02.907
Do not. An eccentric guy, a
rich man from Central America.

57:02.908 --> 57:05.099
Embarking to Ecuador
or to Mexico.

57:05.100 --> 57:08.558
- Does he have to be Chilean?
- In those outfits? I doubt that.

57:09.241 --> 57:12.599
Do not shrink your belly. Release.

57:12.600 --> 57:14.866
- As?
- Release the air.

57:18.624 --> 57:19.824
That.

57:19.825 --> 57:21.640
Do not tell anyone my secret.

57:21.641 --> 57:24.533
Do not worry. No one cares.

57:26.850 --> 57:31.282
"He danced in Vin م del Mar
surrounded by jewels and goblets.

57:31.283 --> 57:35.450
But the black eyes stare
through the black night..."

57:42.416 --> 57:46.990
"But the man who caresses
you stops by the desert.

57:46.991 --> 57:51.991
Near the sea coast, in a world
devastated by death..."

58:00.058 --> 58:02.491
"Every people with their pain..."

58:24.325 --> 58:25.625
Don Pablo?

58:34.766 --> 58:35.966
Don Pablo?

58:54.708 --> 58:55.908
Gentleman!

58:57.616 --> 58:58.816
Gentleman!

59:04.350 --> 59:06.058
Sorry, I do not have anything.

59:41.600 --> 59:44.133
The smart cop smells
the Asian odor.

59:45.958 --> 59:47.258
He is close.

59:57.958 --> 59:59.457
Where were you?

59:59.458 --> 01:00:00.990
They found us. Let's go.

01:00:00.991 --> 01:00:03.200
Not yet. We're lost.

01:00:05.416 --> 01:00:06.716
Where are we?

01:00:13.500 --> 01:00:16.825
- I said it was a good idea.
"Still, it was interesting.

01:00:17.391 --> 01:00:19.825
To write well, you must
know how to delete.

01:00:45.391 --> 01:00:47.925
There is no terror to this persecution.

01:01:16.283 --> 01:01:17.583
Why do I read this?

01:01:19.966 --> 01:01:21.166
I want to know.

01:01:22.633 --> 01:01:24.341
What is your novel about?

01:01:33.308 --> 01:01:36.199
The poet has the fever
of the artistic spirits

01:01:36.200 --> 01:01:39.108
Who think the world is
something they have imagined.

01:01:57.525 --> 01:01:58.840
The flies.

01:01:58.841 --> 01:02:00.833
Again, a swarm of flies.

01:02:03.625 --> 01:02:04.825
What is it?

01:02:05.516 --> 01:02:07.700
The last column of the Red Army?

01:03:03.125 --> 01:03:04.325
It's here.

01:03:11.875 --> 01:03:13.758
Ordinary little man.

01:03:14.158 --> 01:03:15.740
Almost every night,

01:03:15.741 --> 01:03:17.657
The president sleeps
like a child.

01:03:17.658 --> 01:03:21.890
However, whenever you eat
escargot before bed,

01:03:21.891 --> 01:03:23.650
Must dream about Neruda.

01:03:25.208 --> 01:03:26.508
Senator!

01:03:28.125 --> 01:03:29.558
Let's take another turn.

01:03:48.590 --> 01:03:50.782
- Enough, Senator!
- Fuck.

01:03:50.783 --> 01:03:53.975
Here we are, Gabriel
Gonzales of shit!

01:04:14.500 --> 01:04:16.141
- Pablo.
- Jorge, how are you?

01:04:20.333 --> 01:04:22.583
We have a plan to get
you out of Chile.

01:04:23.225 --> 01:04:25.057
"Does the Party know?"
- Of course you know.

01:04:25.058 --> 01:04:26.891
The Secretary-General agrees.

01:04:31.116 --> 01:04:32.316
I'll go.

01:04:34.016 --> 01:04:36.791
No, drink something.

01:04:36.792 --> 01:04:39.850
- No, thank you.
"Do not you want to eat anything?"

01:04:40.808 --> 01:04:42.582
See you tomorrow?

01:04:42.583 --> 01:04:44.558
- I do not think so.
- As?

01:04:45.750 --> 01:04:48.165
I'm going to ask the
Party to let me go.

01:04:48.166 --> 01:04:51.041
- Do not be an idiot, Jara.
- Please...

01:04:52.141 --> 01:04:55.849
This escape from the
south seems very risky.

01:04:55.850 --> 01:04:58.765
"You're not a country man.
"It was the Party's decision.

01:04:58.766 --> 01:05:01.015
But the decision is up to you.

01:05:01.016 --> 01:05:03.282
"You accept it or not.
- I already accepted.

01:05:03.283 --> 01:05:06.099
Why do not you listen
to what he's saying?

01:05:06.100 --> 01:05:08.808
I know what I do with my life.

01:05:09.766 --> 01:05:11.674
They're all trapped but me.

01:05:11.675 --> 01:05:15.165
You think I'm a king?
What are you waiting for?

01:05:15.166 --> 01:05:17.833
- In this case, stay.
- I can 't.

01:05:18.583 --> 01:05:20.933
I can not stay, I must run away.

01:05:22.916 --> 01:05:24.983
It is that you want
a grand escape.

01:05:28.418 --> 01:05:29.618
Is not it?

01:05:30.458 --> 01:05:33.374
I will not get into the game
of these fucking fascists.

01:05:33.375 --> 01:05:35.474
I'll be their worst nightmare.

01:05:35.475 --> 01:05:38.557
For this, I have to
be a popular giant.

01:05:38.558 --> 01:05:40.057
You can not do that.

01:05:40.058 --> 01:05:42.207
- I already did.
- You can not do that.

01:05:42.208 --> 01:05:46.099
Will you say that you used
this chase as an excuse

01:05:46.100 --> 01:05:48.265
To become a saint.

01:05:48.266 --> 01:05:50.140
That we were never repressed.

01:05:50.141 --> 01:05:52.850
That we like to live and suffer.

01:05:53.766 --> 01:05:56.208
But they're really killing us.

01:05:58.083 --> 01:06:01.725
See, I ask you to be a
little more humble.

01:06:07.733 --> 01:06:09.233
Good luck on your trip.

01:06:44.083 --> 01:06:46.683
"What's the matter with you?"
- As well?

01:06:47.375 --> 01:06:49.365
Do you know what to do with your life?

01:06:50.066 --> 01:06:52.224
Delia, please.

01:06:52.225 --> 01:06:54.932
- People will notice.
"Realize what?"

01:06:54.933 --> 01:06:56.265
That the artist here is me.

01:06:56.266 --> 01:06:58.265
- No, the artist is me!
- It's me.

01:06:58.266 --> 01:07:01.057
- The artist here is me!
"You are nothing, Pablo.

01:07:01.058 --> 01:07:03.182
What's the story
of being a giant?

01:07:03.183 --> 01:07:05.549
It is what it is for me to be.

01:07:05.550 --> 01:07:08.724
- You do not know?
- Please, Pablo.

01:07:08.725 --> 01:07:11.265
If you do not like it,
walk out that door.

01:07:11.266 --> 01:07:13.224
No one is chasing you.

01:07:13.225 --> 01:07:14.682
What's the matter with you?

01:07:14.683 --> 01:07:19.015
You choke me, do not
give me a cent.

01:07:19.016 --> 01:07:20.724
Look at me.

01:07:20.725 --> 01:07:23.682
I was a prince, you made
me turn this around.

01:07:23.683 --> 01:07:25.308
Of course I'm leaving.

01:07:25.850 --> 01:07:27.849
Without life, I'm leaving.

01:07:27.850 --> 01:07:31.265
When you arrest me, I tell you
that you want to be president.

01:07:31.266 --> 01:07:35.199
They will hunt him down and kill him.
She's going to be happy.

01:07:35.200 --> 01:07:38.132
Then I'll hit a river.

01:07:38.133 --> 01:07:41.482
You can kill yourself.
You can kill yourself if you want.

01:07:41.483 --> 01:07:43.975
That's how I write 20
more years about you.

01:08:20.908 --> 01:08:24.099
- Antonio Ruiz Lagorreta.
- Ornit soon.

01:08:24.100 --> 01:08:27.846
Ant, I thought I was
going to die with you.

01:08:27.848 --> 01:08:29.721
You gave me everything.

01:08:29.723 --> 01:08:32.991
Without you, I would be nothing.
Neither Communist.

01:08:34.082 --> 01:08:35.282
What?

01:08:36.557 --> 01:08:39.807
If it goes well, if I survive...

01:08:40.723 --> 01:08:42.973
Let's start separating.

01:08:46.832 --> 01:08:50.848
I do not worry about staying,
but I think about you.

01:08:51.432 --> 01:08:56.223
Writing saddens you.
You bury your head in the hands...

01:08:58.098 --> 01:09:00.098
It's lovely to be with you.

01:09:02.557 --> 01:09:04.890
It's like living in a
leafy neighborhood.

01:09:05.416 --> 01:09:06.716
Ant...

01:09:28.457 --> 01:09:31.015
The little ant does
not know what to do.

01:09:31.015 --> 01:09:34.973
Think of the strength of your arm
and the clarity of your brain.

01:09:35.515 --> 01:09:38.598
And realizes that he will
live another 40 years.

01:09:42.622 --> 01:09:44.923
For a minute you
only see red horses.

01:10:21.375 --> 01:10:22.675
Excuse?

01:10:23.957 --> 01:10:26.175
- You may come in.
- Thank you.

01:10:26.850 --> 01:10:28.150
Are you walking?

01:10:29.682 --> 01:10:31.350
- No.
- What is it?

01:10:32.141 --> 01:10:37.175
It is an arrest warrant issued
by the Chilean National Police.

01:10:38.557 --> 01:10:40.807
- No, but...
- No.

01:10:41.565 --> 01:10:42.865
- No.
- No.

01:10:43.225 --> 01:10:47.141
I am a person who dies
but is not arrested.

01:10:48.557 --> 01:10:49.857
Where is he?

01:10:50.391 --> 01:10:52.641
- It's not here.
- At where?

01:10:55.875 --> 01:10:57.516
You do not understand it, do you?

01:10:59.457 --> 01:11:02.681
- You do not understand anything.
- What?

01:11:02.682 --> 01:11:06.207
In this fiction, we all revolve
around the protagonist.

01:11:07.791 --> 01:11:10.766
- As?
- Books, for example.

01:11:12.432 --> 01:11:13.732
This one...

01:11:15.975 --> 01:11:17.874
That you were reading.

01:11:17.875 --> 01:11:19.275
THE ANGEL DARK

01:11:20.557 --> 01:11:23.806
There is a pursuer, a fugitive,

01:11:23.807 --> 01:11:26.640
One principal and one secondary.

01:11:28.266 --> 01:11:30.849
No, but I...

01:11:30.850 --> 01:11:33.600
I'm no secondary character.

01:11:35.307 --> 01:11:38.000
Why do you think he
did not kill you?

01:11:39.975 --> 01:11:41.599
Why can not you kill me?

01:11:41.600 --> 01:11:44.575
Could. Practice
shooting every day.

01:11:46.057 --> 01:11:47.707
No, you can not.

01:11:48.416 --> 01:11:49.616
Do not you?

01:11:50.141 --> 01:11:54.306
Not, of course. He wants you
to chase him south. You go?

01:11:54.307 --> 01:11:55.915
Are you okay?

01:11:56.682 --> 01:11:59.640
Did he hurt you?
Hit you?

01:11:59.641 --> 01:12:03.108
No, he asked me to
give you this message.

01:12:03.791 --> 01:12:05.974
If you want, I can kill you.

01:12:05.975 --> 01:12:08.307
I could not do that.

01:12:08.975 --> 01:12:10.332
Of course I can.

01:12:11.600 --> 01:12:13.165
- No.
- Yes.

01:12:13.166 --> 01:12:14.474
- No!
- Of course yes.

01:12:14.475 --> 01:12:16.850
He wrote that a long time ago.

01:12:18.100 --> 01:12:21.432
Have you ever seen
a bored prisoner?

01:12:22.350 --> 01:12:25.140
In your head, you are writing
a fascinating novel.

01:12:25.141 --> 01:12:28.974
He created you, the Trojan policeman.

01:12:28.975 --> 01:12:31.640
He created me, the absurd woman.

01:12:31.641 --> 01:12:33.308
He wrote to himself.

01:12:34.975 --> 01:12:36.825
The depraved fugitive.

01:12:37.225 --> 01:12:42.925
What you're saying
is modern nonsense,

01:12:43.732 --> 01:12:45.640
A golden lamb.

01:12:46.682 --> 01:12:48.640
Do not you like the
way he writes?

01:12:49.387 --> 01:12:50.587
Like.

01:12:51.807 --> 01:12:56.300
Do you think he only
thinks of land and love?

01:12:56.301 --> 01:12:57.640
Do not.

01:12:57.641 --> 01:13:02.508
He thinks of naked women, of
detectives pursuing him...

01:13:03.100 --> 01:13:06.850
He created you
thinking of yourself.

01:13:07.432 --> 01:13:11.390
You, in your house,
reading his poems.

01:13:11.875 --> 01:13:14.107
You, in front of the mirror.

01:13:15.516 --> 01:13:19.474
He created you
watching our feast,

01:13:19.475 --> 01:13:21.682
Immersed in our music.

01:13:22.850 --> 01:13:27.249
Closed in a car,
with empty eyes.

01:13:27.750 --> 01:13:29.725
A dog at night,

01:13:31.141 --> 01:13:33.433
A bird during the day.

01:13:35.391 --> 01:13:38.766
It created you spying, waiting.

01:13:39.725 --> 01:13:43.724
He created you imprisoned,
a furious spy.

01:13:43.725 --> 01:13:47.266
Listening to things
you'll never understand.

01:13:50.582 --> 01:13:53.643
Depreciating ideas and words.

01:13:54.407 --> 01:13:56.720
One hundred meters from life.

01:13:57.400 --> 01:13:59.116
Powerless.

01:13:59.891 --> 01:14:01.308
Freile.

01:14:01.991 --> 01:14:05.683
He created you as the guardian
of an imaginary frontier.

01:14:09.225 --> 01:14:12.407
He thinks of you
thinking of himself.

01:14:12.850 --> 01:14:15.640
All the detectives are in love.

01:14:15.641 --> 01:14:19.725
In all the detective
novels there are beds.

01:14:21.125 --> 01:14:22.325
Right.

01:14:24.057 --> 01:14:25.457
He writes well.

01:14:26.432 --> 01:14:27.832
He created me.

01:14:29.391 --> 01:14:30.691
But I...

01:14:33.100 --> 01:14:35.007
I've held you.

01:14:36.641 --> 01:14:39.091
And in this hug, I'm going
to take him to jail.

01:14:40.307 --> 01:14:44.265
I'll make him sleep
and watch him dream.

01:14:44.266 --> 01:14:46.890
And I'm going to end up
sitting on his chest.

01:14:46.891 --> 01:14:48.600
Then you will chase after him.

01:14:49.432 --> 01:14:52.765
You will chase after him and arrest him.

01:14:54.225 --> 01:14:56.932
Or it will not enter
the history of men.

01:15:06.891 --> 01:15:08.491
Am I a fiction?

01:15:09.057 --> 01:15:10.257
Yes.

01:15:11.307 --> 01:15:13.750
"And you, is it a fiction?"
- No.

01:15:15.100 --> 01:15:17.825
I am real. And I am eternal.

01:15:21.707 --> 01:15:22.907
Excuse.

01:16:06.166 --> 01:16:08.191
Secondary character?

01:16:08.192 --> 01:16:09.724
I?

01:16:09.725 --> 01:16:11.882
Do not. No, sir.

01:16:12.682 --> 01:16:14.182
Because I'll get you.

01:16:48.166 --> 01:16:49.766
I hope you're right.

01:19:28.675 --> 01:19:29.875
Stop the car.

01:19:33.041 --> 01:19:35.640
- The boss is coming.
- Thank you, Manuel.

01:19:35.641 --> 01:19:37.140
"Do you know him?"
- Yes.

01:19:37.141 --> 01:19:39.506
He is my patron, the
owner of this land.

01:19:39.507 --> 01:19:41.015
We're going to have to walk on foot.

01:19:41.016 --> 01:19:43.991
Does he know everything?
You can call the police.

01:19:48.207 --> 01:19:50.140
When do we go horseback riding?

01:19:51.182 --> 01:19:52.482
Not yet.

01:19:55.941 --> 01:19:57.725
I would eat a whole pig.

01:20:52.250 --> 01:20:54.681
Good afternoon, Don Ricardo.
Good afternoon, ma'am.

01:20:54.682 --> 01:20:56.349
This is Antonio.

01:20:56.350 --> 01:20:57.966
How are you, sir?

01:21:00.291 --> 01:21:01.591
Good afternoon.

01:21:05.600 --> 01:21:07.290
Yes sir?

01:21:07.291 --> 01:21:09.906
I want to know if you could
welcome me to your house?

01:21:09.907 --> 01:21:12.306
Not to mention the patron, of course.

01:21:12.307 --> 01:21:14.665
"Did you kill anyone?"
- No.

01:21:15.932 --> 01:21:18.740
Yes. Writing.

01:21:19.975 --> 01:21:21.632
I'm always writing.

01:21:50.475 --> 01:21:53.725
For many years Neruda has
eaten this same burnt land.

01:21:55.350 --> 01:21:57.050
You must like this bed.

01:21:58.057 --> 01:22:01.265
She would sleep happily
there, hugging her daughter.

01:22:05.850 --> 01:22:09.132
Right now, I just
want you to hold me.

01:22:16.832 --> 01:22:18.825
- Sir.
- Good afternoon.

01:22:23.807 --> 01:22:25.825
- Are you lost?
- No.

01:22:26.475 --> 01:22:29.541
Did not finish

01:22:30.266 --> 01:22:31.800
Do you know where I can...?

01:22:34.307 --> 01:22:35.507
Look.

01:22:37.391 --> 01:22:38.825
Seeing the bike for you.

01:22:39.391 --> 01:22:42.640
Last generation vehicle.
From Germany.

01:22:42.641 --> 01:22:45.931
I'll take you to the
boss, he's got gas.

01:22:45.932 --> 01:22:49.033
I do not need gasoline.

01:22:49.507 --> 01:22:51.157
I need a horse.

01:22:51.600 --> 01:22:52.900
Two horses.

01:22:53.725 --> 01:22:56.631
I'm stalking a very
dangerous criminal.

01:22:56.632 --> 01:22:59.890
"And the bike, can I sell it?"
- Of course.

01:23:00.600 --> 01:23:04.225
Of course. As long as they come with me.

01:23:04.707 --> 01:23:06.907
This can be very exciting.

01:23:11.541 --> 01:23:13.865
Hello? President?

01:23:13.866 --> 01:23:15.806
Mr. President?

01:23:15.807 --> 01:23:18.307
Yes, it is Peluchonneau, yes.

01:23:19.475 --> 01:23:21.575
We arrest Senator Neruda.

01:23:23.557 --> 01:23:24.975
Come on, quick!

01:23:25.432 --> 01:23:26.732
The boss is coming.

01:23:48.340 --> 01:23:49.640
Dominguez.

01:23:49.641 --> 01:23:53.215
A feudal lord who invented
capitalism on his land.

01:23:53.216 --> 01:23:57.406
There is a secret trail up the mountain
to bring Argentine contraband.

01:23:57.407 --> 01:23:58.850
Hello, sir.

01:23:59.682 --> 01:24:02.850
This is Mr. Monsalve,
a Mapuche chief.

01:24:03.725 --> 01:24:05.975
We are afraid of these people.

01:24:06.932 --> 01:24:09.015
Are you tired, Mr. Ruiz?

01:24:09.016 --> 01:24:11.256
I'll call him Mr. Ruiz.

01:24:11.257 --> 01:24:15.275
I'm Pedro Dominguez,
owner of this shit here.

01:24:15.932 --> 01:24:18.266
On behalf of the President
of the Republic,

01:24:18.267 --> 01:24:20.500
I'm going to arrest
him for treason.

01:24:25.357 --> 01:24:28.230
"You're on my own day."
"Am I on your custom day?"

01:24:28.231 --> 01:24:29.431
It is.

01:24:29.432 --> 01:24:31.974
"Are you going to get me arrested?"
- No, I'll help you.

01:24:31.975 --> 01:24:34.015
Crossing the ridge.

01:24:34.016 --> 01:24:36.931
Many people die there.
I'll help you.

01:24:36.932 --> 01:24:38.765
You do not want to pay taxes.

01:24:40.141 --> 01:24:43.181
I'm irritated by this
president you elected.

01:24:43.182 --> 01:24:45.581
He thinks that the state
is an enemy of freedom.

01:24:45.582 --> 01:24:47.765
So why will you help me?

01:24:48.354 --> 01:24:49.908
Yes.

01:24:50.475 --> 01:24:53.182
It is more fun to help
than to call the police.

01:24:54.307 --> 01:24:55.765
More fun?

01:24:55.766 --> 01:24:57.474
Yes, more fun.

01:24:57.475 --> 01:25:01.391
Over his shoulders and soul will
stand the future of the Republic.

01:25:04.875 --> 01:25:08.557
The millionaire is always
smarter than the laws.

01:25:21.357 --> 01:25:22.557
Patron.

01:25:23.266 --> 01:25:26.506
A police officer is here
behind the senator.

01:25:26.507 --> 01:25:29.285
- He wants us to show him the trail.
- What's he like?

01:25:29.775 --> 01:25:32.141
Kind of rough, half idiot.

01:25:36.125 --> 01:25:37.641
Araucania.

01:25:38.600 --> 01:25:40.503
A land without a temple.

01:25:41.307 --> 01:25:43.140
Trees and cold.

01:25:43.891 --> 01:25:46.265
It is said that the
conquistadors wept

01:25:46.266 --> 01:25:48.824
When a Mapuche patrol arrived.

01:25:48.825 --> 01:25:51.707
They were more afraid of the
Indians than of the Moors.

01:25:53.350 --> 01:25:55.516
Now it is a land of peace.

01:25:56.307 --> 01:25:59.040
A land of clay and work.

01:25:59.541 --> 01:26:01.183
The poet writes about it.

01:26:02.441 --> 01:26:04.850
The suffering of the
poor inspires him.

01:27:37.457 --> 01:27:39.725
Pablo!

01:28:19.125 --> 01:28:21.057
Hide! Hide!

01:28:41.041 --> 01:28:42.341
Pablo...

01:28:44.100 --> 01:28:45.400
I'm seeing you.

01:28:47.807 --> 01:28:49.382
I hear you gasp.

01:28:59.957 --> 01:29:02.825
The middle one, the fat one.

01:29:04.475 --> 01:29:09.107
I go from the left, you
see from the right.

01:29:10.141 --> 01:29:13.306
I'm going to shoot the horse's
head so I'll die soon.

01:29:13.307 --> 01:29:16.132
You come and grab it.

01:29:20.500 --> 01:29:22.581
It's going to be very impressive.

01:29:22.582 --> 01:29:25.056
You think they will not shoot?

01:29:25.057 --> 01:29:26.357
Do not.

01:29:27.641 --> 01:29:30.391
Because the animals
will run scared.

01:29:31.850 --> 01:29:33.775
It's going to be a chain reaction.

01:29:34.391 --> 01:29:35.931
Meanwhile...

01:29:35.932 --> 01:29:38.331
I'll come forward.

01:29:38.332 --> 01:29:40.615
It's good to be a cop, right?

01:29:40.616 --> 01:29:42.325
Right. Let's go.

01:29:48.166 --> 01:29:49.600
I'm sorry, sir.

01:30:22.457 --> 01:30:26.600
The shit of the traitor Gonzales
Videla is me, and I came this far.

01:30:28.182 --> 01:30:31.507
Me, the skinny, the bony.

01:30:50.100 --> 01:30:54.557
In this white bed, I make a
toast to the last months.

01:30:54.975 --> 01:30:58.100
I only have one bullet,
passionate boar.

01:30:58.932 --> 01:31:03.007
But do not worry.
With the cold, you will not feel it.

01:31:03.008 --> 01:31:04.820
Pablo!

01:31:11.582 --> 01:31:13.432
Why does he come to me?

01:31:14.100 --> 01:31:15.400
Are not you afraid?

01:31:17.050 --> 01:31:18.505
Pablo, where are you going?

01:31:18.506 --> 01:31:19.806
But he is curious.

01:31:19.807 --> 01:31:22.099
Pablo, come on. Pablo!

01:31:22.100 --> 01:31:23.432
He wants to see me.

01:31:24.350 --> 01:31:26.550
How could he not see
the end of his story?

01:31:51.041 --> 01:31:52.600
Where are you going, man?

01:31:58.916 --> 01:32:00.316
He gave me a hug.

01:32:03.250 --> 01:32:04.650
Talked to me.

01:32:06.350 --> 01:32:07.907
And she danced with me.

01:32:10.016 --> 01:32:12.758
I pursued the guide, but I
do not know how to fly.

01:32:14.100 --> 01:32:15.500
I'm far away.

01:32:17.350 --> 01:32:20.191
I can only go back to the
bottom of the earth.

01:32:23.182 --> 01:32:25.950
I lived believing I
was a Peluchonneau.

01:32:26.932 --> 01:32:29.090
Son of a police uniform.

01:32:31.600 --> 01:32:33.266
But now...

01:32:34.432 --> 01:32:37.032
I think maybe I was a Neruda.

01:32:38.266 --> 01:32:39.700
A son of the people.

01:32:41.057 --> 01:32:43.407
Maybe my father
lived on his knees,

01:32:44.016 --> 01:32:45.750
With the dirty face.

01:32:47.016 --> 01:32:49.281
Maybe put together four coins

01:32:49.282 --> 01:32:52.232
And paid to sweat the
back of my hand.

01:32:54.932 --> 01:32:56.975
Maybe I'm a son of the wheat.

01:32:57.850 --> 01:33:01.516
Another black head among
millions of black heads.

01:33:02.932 --> 01:33:04.931
But I'm going to die white,

01:33:04.932 --> 01:33:07.475
Because nobody else
persecuted the poet.

01:33:09.100 --> 01:33:11.432
No one else terrified
him in the snow.

01:33:12.600 --> 01:33:15.116
No one else made him
gasp regretfully.

01:33:16.391 --> 01:33:18.758
No one else accompanied
him on his trip.

01:33:21.957 --> 01:33:24.032
It does not matter
that you wrote to me,

01:33:24.782 --> 01:33:27.275
That made me a
secondary character.

01:33:43.957 --> 01:33:45.457
I wrote myself too.

01:33:47.391 --> 01:33:48.866
Lousy way.

01:33:50.350 --> 01:33:52.157
I invented myself without life,

01:33:52.766 --> 01:33:55.675
Alone, without love.

01:33:57.725 --> 01:34:00.232
But the poet invented me furiously,

01:34:00.766 --> 01:34:02.266
Full of wind.

01:34:03.600 --> 01:34:06.175
He wrote me to a fabulous death.

01:34:07.600 --> 01:34:09.216
A police death.

01:34:14.032 --> 01:34:17.050
Slow, cold.

01:34:18.391 --> 01:34:20.200
With red details,

01:34:21.057 --> 01:34:22.457
With music,

01:34:23.307 --> 01:34:24.865
with animals,

01:34:25.766 --> 01:34:27.166
With trees,

01:34:28.600 --> 01:34:30.000
With poetry.

01:35:43.041 --> 01:35:44.441
Do you know him?

01:35:51.100 --> 01:35:52.300
Do not.

01:35:58.432 --> 01:35:59.632
Yes...

01:36:00.932 --> 01:36:02.365
Yes I know.

01:36:05.500 --> 01:36:07.057
This is my inspector.

01:36:08.266 --> 01:36:09.666
My pursuer.

01:36:11.557 --> 01:36:13.450
My uniform ghost.

01:36:18.307 --> 01:36:20.656
I dream about him and
he dreams about me.

01:36:20.657 --> 01:36:23.265
He watches over me,
knows my back.

01:36:25.516 --> 01:36:27.600
Look what you wrote, officer.

01:36:28.975 --> 01:36:31.182
You wrote the snow
and the horses.

01:36:32.432 --> 01:36:33.990
You raise Me Up.

01:36:41.850 --> 01:36:43.782
Now you do not even feel the cold.

01:36:51.166 --> 01:36:52.566
We have to take him.

01:36:54.682 --> 01:36:56.325
Alert the muleteers.

01:37:12.932 --> 01:37:15.365
I feel the heart
beat of this horse.

01:37:17.225 --> 01:37:19.491
I feel my own heart, too.

01:37:21.100 --> 01:37:22.532
Because they did not kill me.

01:37:24.100 --> 01:37:26.566
They did not kill me
with a blow to the head.

01:37:27.166 --> 01:37:28.991
- Are you breathing?
- No.

01:37:44.916 --> 01:37:47.931
Mr. Picasso, tell me
what happened to him.

01:37:47.932 --> 01:37:49.890
For almost two years,

01:37:49.891 --> 01:37:54.381
Neruda headed the Chilean
resistance in the clandestine.

01:37:54.382 --> 01:37:58.349
The political police chased
him into the mountains.

01:37:58.350 --> 01:38:01.599
But the poet crossed the Andes,

01:38:01.600 --> 01:38:04.557
Disappeared in the snow
and came to heaven.

01:38:07.225 --> 01:38:10.724
Mr. Neruda, did you write
in the underground?

01:38:10.725 --> 01:38:11.925
Forgiveness?

01:38:11.926 --> 01:38:17.391
Are you afraid that your political
figure will overlap your poetry?

01:38:18.842 --> 01:38:20.042
Do not.

01:38:21.016 --> 01:38:22.833
I'm not afraid.

01:38:23.516 --> 01:38:25.349
It turns out that...

01:38:25.350 --> 01:38:29.932
Sometimes I feel like I'm
freezing in the snow.

01:38:30.641 --> 01:38:33.015
I dream. I dream with this.

01:38:33.016 --> 01:38:36.700
- Cold dead?
- No, dead with one shot.

01:38:37.432 --> 01:38:38.931
There's a man...

01:38:38.932 --> 01:38:42.432
Who was about to kill me.

01:38:43.141 --> 01:38:46.058
"Is he still pursuing you?"
- It's possible.

01:38:47.100 --> 01:38:50.407
- Who is it?
"A policeman, miss.

01:38:51.807 --> 01:38:54.807
Maybe he's around, watching us.

01:39:12.875 --> 01:39:14.866
No one will know that I existed.

01:39:18.832 --> 01:39:21.032
Say my name. Say it!

01:39:24.875 --> 01:39:26.275
Say my name.

01:39:28.141 --> 01:39:29.700
Say my name!

01:39:31.600 --> 01:39:33.432
His name was Oscar.

01:39:34.682 --> 01:39:37.056
Oscar Peluchonneau.

01:39:37.057 --> 01:39:40.431
- You said!
- Peluchonneau.

01:39:40.432 --> 01:39:41.765
You said my name!

01:39:41.766 --> 01:39:44.531
Write: Peluchonneau.

01:39:44.532 --> 01:39:47.032
I'm not a secondary character.

01:39:49.141 --> 01:39:53.265
Many men of my country
are in prison,

01:39:53.266 --> 01:39:55.140
Tortured, exiled.

01:39:55.141 --> 01:39:57.100
I'm just one of them.

01:39:57.932 --> 01:40:01.731
Because I've always been
a prisoner with them.

01:40:02.332 --> 01:40:06.556
Why did he do all this?
For your people.

01:40:06.557 --> 01:40:10.265
The poet gave them words
to count their lives.

01:40:10.266 --> 01:40:11.866
Their lives are hard.

01:40:13.266 --> 01:40:16.683
These words made sense to
his terrifying dreams.

01:40:17.641 --> 01:40:21.350
That's why he did everything,
so they could talk.

01:40:22.250 --> 01:40:25.225
They can already be quoted as
being trampled by history.

01:40:26.266 --> 01:40:28.640
They do not remember
the poems of love,

01:40:28.641 --> 01:40:30.780
S of the fairy tales.

01:40:31.432 --> 01:40:33.638
Unrecognizable Poems...

01:40:34.225 --> 01:40:36.765
Poems of an imaginary future.

01:40:36.766 --> 01:40:39.806
"I can write the saddest
poem of all tonight..."

01:40:39.807 --> 01:40:43.023
Wonderful!

01:40:45.500 --> 01:40:47.307
Neruda made me eternal.

01:40:48.932 --> 01:40:50.600
Your art gave me life.

01:40:59.250 --> 01:41:00.807
I was from paper...

01:41:02.850 --> 01:41:04.732
And now I am of blood.

01:41:25.100 --> 01:41:28.516
I can write the saddest
poem of all tonight...

